Here is an example of a JSON Schema for a Beta Cruiser:
```json
{
    "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2019-09/schema",
    "title": "Beta Cruiser",
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "name": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "crew": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
                "type": "object",
                "properties": {
                    "id": {
                        "type": "integer"
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
```
This JSON Schema defines the properties of a Beta Cruiser, which consists of a name (a string) and a crew (an array of objects). Each object in the crew has an id property (an integer).

Note that this is just an example; you can modify it to suit your needs. For example, you might want to add more properties or change the types of the properties. You can also use placeholders like "[...]" to represent arrays or other complex data structures.

